fields.value: Centre de Investigaciones sobre la Realidad Social (CIRES) [Spain], 1991 (M469V1)

authorName.value: Centro de Estudios sobre la Realidad Social [Spain]

dsDescriptionValue.value:
The CIRES studies are conducted over a period of months in 1991. In 1991 the studies explore supranational identification, use of time, attitudes toward immigrants, social inequalities based on sex and age, education and social mobility, political culture, economic attitudes and behavior, life styles, and drugs as a social problem. Studies are conducted under the supervision of Juan Diez Nicols.

January Sample: 1.200 persons of either sex, 18 years old and over, living in Spain. Random sample, stratified by autonomous regions and municipalities according to their size. Field Research: Conducted through personal interview at the interviewees' homes, by Redex Network (IOPE-ETMAR). Supervision by A.S.E.P of 20% of the interviews.

February Sample: 1.200 persons of either sex, 18 years old and over, living in Spain. Random sample, stratified by autonomous regions and municipalities according to their size. Field Research: Conducted through personal interview at the interviewees' homes, by Intercampo S.A. . Supervision by A.S.E.P of 20% of the interviews.

March Sample: 1.200 persons of either sex, 18 years old and over, living in Spain. Random sample, stratified by autonomous regions and municipalities according to their size. Field Research: Conducted through personal interview at the interviewees' homes, by Intercampo S.A. . Supervision by A.S.E.P of 20% of the interviews.

April Sample: 1.200 persons of either sex, 18 years old and over, living in Spain. Random sample, stratified by autonomous regions and municipalities according to their size. Field Research: Conducted through personal interview at the interviewees' homes, by Intercampo S.A. . Supervision by A.S.E.P of 20% of the interviews.

May Sample: 1.200 persons of either sex, 18 years old and over, living in Spain. Random sample, stratified by autonomous regions and municipalities according to their size. Field Research: Conducted through personal interview at the interviewees' homes, by Intercampo S.A. . Supervision by A.S.E.P of 20% of the interviews.

June Field Research: Conducted from the June 6th to 13th 1991, through personal interview at the interviewees' homes, by Intercampo S.A. . Supervision by A.S.E.P of 20% of the interviews. Data Proceesing: Designed and conducted by A.S.E.P., with its own software, elaborated by J.D. Systems, Ltd.

July Sample: 1.200 persons of either sex, 18 years old and over, living in Spain. Random sample, stratified by autonomous regions and municipalities according to their size. Field Research: Conducted through personal interview at the interviewees' homes, by Intercampo S.A. . Supervision by A.S.E.P of 20% of the interviews.

October Sample: 1.200 persons of either sex, 18 years old and over, living in Spain. Random sample, stratified by autonomous regions and municipalities according to their size. Field Research: Conducted through personal interview at the interviewees' homes, by Intercampo S.A. . Supervision by A.S.E.P of 20% of the interviews.

November Sample: 1.200 persons of either sex, 18 years old and over, living in Spain. Random sample, stratified by autonomous regions and municipalities according to their size. Field Research: Conducted through personal interview at the interviewees' homes, by Intercampo S.A. . Supervision by A.S.E.P of 20% of the interviews.

December Sample: 1.200 persons of either sex, 18 years old and over, living in Spain. Random sample, stratified by autonomous regions and municipalities according to their size. Field Research: Conducted through personal interview at the interviewees' homes, by Intercampo S.A. . Supervision by A.S.E.P of 20% of the interviews.
